{
  "video_id": "1aYcup5k7uc",
  "title": "How to Choose Leica M Lenses",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 10950.0,
      "end_time": 13657.0,
      "text": "Dan Tamarkin here from Tamarkin Camera in downtown Chicago"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 13660.0,
      "end_time": 17240.0,
      "text": "to talk a little bit about how to choose a Leica M lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18480.0,
      "end_time": 21640.0,
      "text": "The first thing to understand about Leica M cameras"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22100.0,
      "end_time": 24120.0,
      "text": "is that they&#39;re range finder cameras,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24180.0,
      "end_time": 27750.0,
      "text": "which means you&#39;re looking through this little window."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27750.0,
      "end_time": 30660.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re not actually looking through the lens itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30660.0,
      "end_time": 33200.0,
      "text": "As you can see, the lens is placed here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33220.0,
      "end_time": 35680.0,
      "text": "and the viewfinder is here."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35940.0,
      "end_time": 37800.0,
      "text": "We do have parallax correction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37800.0,
      "end_time": 39899.0,
      "text": "which allows you to focus the lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39900.0,
      "end_time": 42680.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s very important to understand, in choosing Leica lenses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 42960.0,
      "end_time": 44820.0,
      "text": "that there are no zooms because"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44840.0,
      "end_time": 47180.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re simply looking through this piece of glass,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47700.0,
      "end_time": 50640.0,
      "text": "which has these little bright frame lines inside of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51320.0,
      "end_time": 53000.0,
      "text": "As you mount different lens models,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53000.0,
      "end_time": 56720.0,
      "text": "the proper bright frame lines appear up here in the range finder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56820.0,
      "end_time": 58980.0,
      "text": "which allows you to compose your image."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58980.0,
      "end_time": 62339.0,
      "text": "However, you can only have one lens on the camera at a time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 62460.0,
      "end_time": 63680.0,
      "text": "so choosing the Leica lens"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 63680.0,
      "end_time": 66180.0,
      "text": "that you will be using to compose your images"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 66220.0,
      "end_time": 67460.0,
      "text": "is very important."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 68460.0,
      "end_time": 70300.0,
      "text": "Understanding how the range finder works"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 70300.0,
      "end_time": 72679.0,
      "text": "is the first step in choosing a Leica lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 73700.0,
      "end_time": 76279.0,
      "text": "Here, on the table, we have a number of 50mm lenses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 76280.0,
      "end_time": 84100.0,
      "text": "some from the 1950s, 1970s, 80, 90s, currently manufactured."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84760.0,
      "end_time": 86200.0,
      "text": "These are F2 lenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 86140.0,
      "end_time": 87860.0,
      "text": "These are F1.4 lenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 88600.0,
      "end_time": 90340.0,
      "text": "And these are faster Noctilux lenses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 90720.0,
      "end_time": 92620.0,
      "text": "which we will talk about in a moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 93380.0,
      "end_time": 95140.0,
      "text": "The important thing to also understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 95141.0,
      "end_time": 96520.0,
      "text": "about range finder lenses"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 96520.0,
      "end_time": 98660.0,
      "text": "is that you have a mechanical connection"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 98660.0,
      "end_time": 99920.0,
      "text": "when you mount the lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 100300.0,
      "end_time": 102259.0,
      "text": "All of the lenses snap right into the body,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 102260.0,
      "end_time": 104740.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re very, very compact."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 104840.0,
      "end_time": 108950.0,
      "text": "They all have focus, and they all have aperture."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 108950.0,
      "end_time": 113390.0,
      "text": "These are the important facets of any photographic lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 113400.0,
      "end_time": 114500.0,
      "text": "The way that the system works"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 115400.0,
      "end_time": 118520.0,
      "text": "is that you have this mechanical connection here."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 118520.0,
      "end_time": 119820.0,
      "text": "As you focus the lens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 119820.0,
      "end_time": 122520.0,
      "text": "this little cam moves in and out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 122520.0,
      "end_time": 125700.0,
      "text": "and it, in turn, moves this little lever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 126480.0,
      "end_time": 128920.0,
      "text": "which is what you use to focus."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 128919.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132660.0,
      "text": "The range finder is calibrated to focus"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 132660.0,
      "end_time": 135790.0,
      "text": "in this connection."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 136720.0,
      "end_time": 138500.0,
      "text": "Why do people use Leica lenses?"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 138600.0,
      "end_time": 141000.0,
      "text": "Well, because they&#39;re extremely compact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 141400.0,
      "end_time": 142960.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re extremely well-made,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 143180.0,
      "end_time": 145280.0,
      "text": "and the optics are the best in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 148460.0,
      "end_time": 151520.0,
      "text": "Why do all Leica users use these funny words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 151520.0,
      "end_time": 155340.0,
      "text": "like Summicron, Summilux, Elmarit, and Noctilux?"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 156120.0,
      "end_time": 158540.0,
      "text": "All of these terms are trademark Leica terms"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 158540.0,
      "end_time": 160880.0,
      "text": "that refer to F-stop of the lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 161000.0,
      "end_time": 162800.0,
      "text": "For example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 163800.0,
      "end_time": 165280.0,
      "text": "all Summicrons are F-2--"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 166000.0,
      "end_time": 169220.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the widest aperture that the lens has."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 172460.0,
      "end_time": 173900.0,
      "text": "So, what do these words mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 174800.0,
      "end_time": 175780.0,
      "text": "Summicron = F-2."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 176540.0,
      "end_time": 178900.0,
      "text": "Summilux = F1.4."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 179860.0,
      "end_time": 185580.0,
      "text": "Noctilux can be F1.2, F1 or .95,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 185580.0,
      "end_time": 187580.0,
      "text": "which is the fastest production lens in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 188640.0,
      "end_time": 191359.0,
      "text": "All of these Leica M lenses are extremely compact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 191980.0,
      "end_time": 195799.0,
      "text": "and they all work on the older M cameras,,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 196160.0,
      "end_time": 197799.0,
      "text": "newer M cameras,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 197800.0,
      "end_time": 200220.0,
      "text": "and even digital M cameras."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 200540.0,
      "end_time": 204959.0,
      "text": "So, a lens that was made in the 1950s"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 204960.0,
      "end_time": 210600.0,
      "text": "will work just fine on a modern Leica M digital camera."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 211100.0,
      "end_time": 212880.0,
      "text": "Nonetheless, it&#39;s very important to choose"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 212880.0,
      "end_time": 214540.0,
      "text": "the right focal length for you."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 216640.0,
      "end_time": 218100.0,
      "text": "There are two other terms"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 218100.0,
      "end_time": 221840.0,
      "text": "that Leica uses in their manufacturing of their lenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 221860.0,
      "end_time": 222920.0,
      "text": "One is APO,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 222920.0,
      "end_time": 225579.0,
      "text": "which stands for apochromatically corrected,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 226480.0,
      "end_time": 228140.0,
      "text": "and then aspherical (ASPH)."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 229820.0,
      "end_time": 232739.0,
      "text": "Apochromatic correction addresses an anomaly"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 232780.0,
      "end_time": 235114.0,
      "text": "called chromatic aberration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 235114.0,
      "end_time": 239549.0,
      "text": "or colors shift and are not rendered necessarily correctly."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 239549.0,
      "end_time": 242580.0,
      "text": "You can get color fringing and all kinds of other effects"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 242580.0,
      "end_time": 244170.0,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t really like."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 244170.0,
      "end_time": 246590.0,
      "text": "So, some of the lenses that Leica designs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 246600.0,
      "end_time": 250180.0,
      "text": "such as the APO aspherical 50mm Summicron,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 250180.0,
      "end_time": 252780.0,
      "text": "are corrected for color"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 252920.0,
      "end_time": 254739.0,
      "text": "and all of the light rays to meet on the film plane"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 254740.0,
      "end_time": 256900.0,
      "text": "at exactly the same time."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 256899.0,
      "end_time": 259640.0,
      "text": "APO stands for apochromatically corrected,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 259839.0,
      "end_time": 262159.0,
      "text": "and there is benefit in having an APO lens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 262160.0,
      "end_time": 263660.0,
      "text": "even if you&#39;re shooting black and white."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 263660.0,
      "end_time": 267120.0,
      "text": "It means that the lens renders more sharply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 267120.0,
      "end_time": 270720.0,
      "text": "with high contrast, all kinds of good things."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 270720.0,
      "end_time": 275420.0,
      "text": "The other designation addresses spherical aberration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 275420.0,
      "end_time": 278222.0,
      "text": "which is the other kind of aberration that"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 278222.0,
      "end_time": 280900.0,
      "text": "happens in 35mm photography."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 280900.0,
      "end_time": 281780.0,
      "text": "The important thing to understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 281780.0,
      "end_time": 285500.0,
      "text": "is that aspherical lenses generally are less prone to flare,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 285500.0,
      "end_time": 287800.0,
      "text": "have a flatter field,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 287800.0,
      "end_time": 291320.0,
      "text": "and the edges of the photograph are generally sharper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 291320.0,
      "end_time": 295600.0,
      "text": "higher contrast, and with better color rendering."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 295600.0,
      "end_time": 297680.0,
      "text": "However, the important thing to understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 297680.0,
      "end_time": 299160.0,
      "text": "in choosing a Leica lens"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 299340.0,
      "end_time": 300700.0,
      "text": "is that these are little gems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 301400.0,
      "end_time": 304240.0,
      "text": "and it doesn&#39;t matter whether you have some aspherical"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 304240.0,
      "end_time": 305560.0,
      "text": "or something that&#39;s vintage--"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 305560.0,
      "end_time": 307480.0,
      "text": "they all make fabulous images,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 307480.0,
      "end_time": 311580.0,
      "text": "and you basically get higher contrast as you get more modern."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 311580.0,
      "end_time": 315740.0,
      "text": "So, as you continue to embark on your Leica journey,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 315740.0,
      "end_time": 318800.0,
      "text": "please do contact us at tamarkin.com"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 318800.0,
      "end_time": 321920.0,
      "text": "or by dialing (800) BUY-LEICA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 321920.0,
      "end_time": 325500.0,
      "text": "so we can help you choose exactly the right camera"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 325840.0,
      "end_time": 328380.0,
      "text": "and Leica lens for your photographic journey."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 328390.0,
      "end_time": 331280.0,
      "text": "Also, on our website, tamarkin.com,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 331280.0,
      "end_time": 333929.0,
      "text": "you can look at some of the differences between"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 333930.0,
      "end_time": 336360.0,
      "text": "the vintage models and more modern models,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 336660.0,
      "end_time": 339260.0,
      "text": "as well as the Leica digital cameras,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 340540.0,
      "end_time": 343720.0,
      "text": "and even some of the rare, collectable cameras"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 344260.0,
      "end_time": 345780.0,
      "text": "that we have to offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 346740.0,
      "end_time": 348700.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re more than happy to share our knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 348700.0,
      "end_time": 351620.0,
      "text": "of every photographic Leica device that"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 351620.0,
      "end_time": 353920.0,
      "text": "has brought to market since 1925."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 354680.0,
      "end_time": 356580.0,
      "text": "Give us a call or send us an email,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 356860.0,
      "end_time": 358660.0,
      "text": "and let us know how we can help find"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 358660.0,
      "end_time": 360760.0,
      "text": "the right camera and lens for you."
    }
  ]
